<p><span style="font-size:75%;">This is a series showing off news from the site, articles from the past month<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-1" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-1')">1</a></sup>, and fan-content for you to check out and discover! Be sure to leave a comment with your thoughts!</span></p>
<h4><span>Fandom Stuff</span></h4>
<ul>
<li>SCP-FR (French language branch of the SCP Foundation) is running <a href="http://fondationscp.wikidot.com/le-concours-des-404-ans">a contest</a> for the SCP-404-FR slot. Participants are asked to write about &quot;An error, something that caused one or the consequences of one&quot;. The visual design of the contest hub is worth checking out whether you speak French or not.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>SCP-EN (English, this wiki) is conducting another <a href="/instagram-fan-art-contest-fall-2020">Instagram Fan Art Contest</a>.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>SCP-PL (Polish) is running the inventive <a href="http://scp-pl.wikidot.com/rezurekcja-usunietych">Resurrecting The Deleted</a> contest. Participants pick a title of a work from the Deletions Log, and write an article using said title.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>SCP-KO (Korean) finished its latest <a href="http://ko.scp-wiki.net/bimonthly-contests-2020#toc4">bimonthly contest</a>. The theme of the contest was &quot;Language&quot;.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>SCP-DE (German) concluded its second <a href="http://scp-wiki-de.wikidot.com/halloween-wettbewerb-2020">Halloween contest</a>.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>SCP-IT (Italian) also ran a <a href="http://fondazionescp.wikidot.com/concorso-halloween-2020-dr-zeno">Halloween contest</a> this month.</li>
</ul>
<h4><span>Featured Articles</span></h4>
